1> Constructor is a special kind of method
2> Same name of the class name
3> NO Return type
4> Used to initialize the newly created object
5> When there is NO constructor defined in the class
	Then the default constructor will be provided by the compiler
6> Constructors can be overloaded
new keyword does 3 things
1> creates an Object
2> allocates the memory on heap for an object
3> invoke the constructor to initialize the newly created Object